### Order of Entropy - Wizard
For most wizards channeling the weave is as far as they go. However some wizards dig deeper, channeling a different yet familar energy. Entropy, a force that acts against the weave and magic, the wizards who walk this path balance on a knifes edge. For some this is a means to an end, they don't dig much deeper then the basics but for others they dig even deeper, leeching off the weave to channel powerful forces, forces that are regularly used to strike down the very ones who make regular use of the Weave.


#### Entropic Bolt
At 2nd level you gain the ability to channel the latent force of entropy. You gain access to the firebolt cantrip with the following changes;
it deals force instead of fire damage, its range is reduced to 60 feet, and it is unnaffected by counterspell or antimagic field during its casting.


#### Weave Theft
Also at 2nd level you are not bound by many of the rules that affect most spellcasters. Select a cantrip and 1st level spell of your choice from any class to take. You prepare this spell as normal, it uses intelligence rather then its normal casting ability, and it is treated as a wizard spell for you. Additionally The spells you learn at 7th, and 14th level can come from any classes spell list. You prepare these spells as normal and it uses intelligence rather then its normal casting ability.

#### Entropic Build Up
At 6th level you grow more in tune with the entropic forces of reality, you are able to turn the weapons of your enemy against them. 
When counterspelling or dispelling a spell you gain an amount of Entropic tokens equal to half of the dispelled spells level rounded up with a minimum of 1 token. You can have a maximum number of tokens equal to your double your proficency modifer.

As a bonus action you can spend entropic tokens to restore a spell slot equal to half the entropic tokens spent rounded up. The highest spellslot you can restore is 5th level.

Additionally the damage dice for the cantrip granted by Entropic Bolt increases from D10 to D12.

#### Carve the Weave
Your grip over entropy has strengthened to the point that your very magic is infused with it. At 10th level when you cast a spell you can use your reaction to spend a entropic token to channel entropic energies rather then the weave. Spells cast this way are unaffected by counterspell or antimagic field.

#### Rebuke the Weave
At 14th level as a bonus action, you may expend a spell slot of 7th level or higher to enter an entropic state of being. For one minute you gain a limited magic resistance granting the following effects
- If you are targeted or effected by a spell of third level or lower it instead has no effect for the duration. this effect is increased to 4th level with a 8th level slot consumed and 5th level with a 9th level slot consumed. 
- Your entropic bolt gains advantage on all attack rolls.
- The only spell you may cast is entropic bolt, however the number of times you may cast it with the same action increases according to the spell slot consumed to activate this state as follows: Twice total for 7th level, three times total for 8th level, and 4 times for 9th level.
- Finally you gain a 10ft flying (hover speed) but only if activated with a 9th level slot

When this state ends you gain 2 points of exhaustion.

