### Void Singer - Rogue
For some fortune is what they seek, for others knowledge, and for others still power. Some would call what lurks within the void all three. Those who have delved deep enough to find it sing of what they found. 

#### Lessons of the Void
The whispers of Entropy teach you well. At 3rd level you gain proficency with medium armor, as well as proficiency with all martial and simple weapons.  

Additionally at 9th level you gain proficency with heavy armor and shields.

#### Fed by Blood
Entropy spurs you into battle, and it protects you from harm. At 3rd level when you hit with a sneak attack you may choose to deal half damage, if you do so, you gain temporary hitpoints equal to the damage dealt. You may use this ability a number of times equal your proficency modifier per long rest.

You also gain additional ways to use your Sneak Attack; you don't need advantage on the attack roll to use your Sneak Attack against a creature if 2 or more creatures are within 5 feet of you or a creature that is allied to the creature you are targeting is within 5 feet of that creature and you don't have disadvantage. Finally you can sneak attack with any martial weapon that lacks the reach or heavy property. All other rules for Sneak Attack still apply to you.

#### Song of Recognition
Entropy croons, drawing the attention of all to you. At 9th level as a bonus action you may cause all creatures within 30 feet that are hostile to you to make a Charisma check contested by your own Charisma check. On a failure that creature has disadvantage on all attacks against creatures other then you, additionally allies have advantage against saving throws caused by said creature, This effect lasts for 1 minute. At the end of each of their their turns they may repeat the saving throw. This effect ends if you move more then 15 feet from where you triggered it. You have one use of this, and gain an additional use at 13th and 17th level of this class. You regain any uses expended after a long rest.

#### Instrument of Death
Entropy sings and you are its instrument. At 13th level You gain profiency with Constitution saving throws.

Additonally While Song of Recognition is active, you gain advantage on all attacks against creatures effected by Song of Recognition that failed their saving throw. 



#### Choir of the Void
The whispers of entropy spill out into a chorus of song, you slide through reality striking at your foes regardless of distance. At 17th level when activating Song of Recognition you may choose to enter Choir of the Void. when you do so you gain the following abilities for one minute:
- Your speed falls to 0 feet.
- You gain infinite uses of Fed by Blood.
- Your AC is increased by 3
- As an action you can make a melee attack against a creature under the effects of Song of Recognition regardless of range.

As an action you can end this effect. After activating this feature you may not do so again until long rest.

